00:25:49,622 --> 00:25:54,063
Yeah, my first job before working at the Beezart company was actually in the games industry.

326
00:25:55,339 --> 00:26:01,282
The day-to-day skills that you find yourself using in either industry and either job are remarkably similar.

327
00:26:02,062 --> 00:26:07,684
Things from working with custom story technology, creating responsive and interactive worlds,

328
00:26:07,744 --> 00:26:11,046
communicating with sometimes huge multidisciplinary teams,

329
00:26:11,866 --> 00:26:16,428
understanding guest flow as it pertains to emergent and environmental storytelling,

330
00:26:16,488 --> 00:26:20,930
just creating a backdrop for people to make their own characters and make their own stories.

331
00:26:21,010 --> 00:26:22,811
And obviously it varies depending on...

332
00:26:23,227 --> 00:26:31,809
You're disciplined, but yet your skills are more transferable than you might think as a game designer who might be interested in the world of themed entertainment.

