00:26:42,831 --> 00:26:47,392
And in addition, a lot now have app layers, companion apps that we were talking about, where...

336
00:26:47,912 --> 00:26:49,352
Yeah, they just... they need game developers.

337
00:26:49,412 --> 00:26:53,013
It's a craft you already know, just in a theme park environment.

338
00:26:54,224 --> 00:26:58,549
And one of the things that you may not know if you haven't really looked into this industry

339
00:26:58,729 --> 00:27:01,151
is it's more than just the mouse, right?

340
00:27:01,171 --> 00:27:02,533
It's more than just Disney.

341
00:27:02,593 --> 00:27:06,176
Disney certainly created the themed entertainment industry as we know it.

342
00:27:06,737 --> 00:27:10,761
Then along came Universal over the years and other large companies have done it.

343
00:27:10,921 --> 00:27:16,547
But what people don't necessarily realize is that that has led to a broad...

344
00:27:18,168 --> 00:27:24,211
of immersive theme park-like experiences in other places around the world.

345
00:27:24,671 --> 00:27:29,293
So we've worked on things for Epcot, big fireworks shows for Epcot,

346
00:27:29,313 --> 00:27:33,695
but we've also worked on Space Shuttle Atlantis at Space Station.

347
00:27:33,955 --> 00:27:40,037
Kennedy Space Center. We've been able to create immersive Halloween parties for the White House.

348
00:27:40,378 --> 00:27:46,160
We've worked with helping theme parks in Asia and the Middle East expanding their ideas. We've worked

349
00:27:46,180 --> 00:27:51,882
with the Lego theme parks who are learning to tell the story of how to make a plastic brick

